# Frontend React/TypeScript Conventions

## File organization

- `src/pages/` — route-level components (Home, Results)
- `src/components/` — reusable UI components (FileUpload, ResultRow, StatusBadge, SummaryCards, ProgressBar)
- `src/lib/api.ts` — all backend API calls
- `src/lib/types.ts` — TypeScript interfaces mirroring backend Pydantic schemas

## Type safety

- Always use the interfaces from `src/lib/types.ts` — never use `any` for API data
- Status values are union types: `"met" | "not_met" | "partial"`
- Confidence values are union types: `"high" | "medium" | "low"`
- When backend schemas change, update `types.ts` first, then fix type errors

## Component patterns

- Functional components only
- Colocate component-specific logic; extract shared hooks to `src/lib/` or `src/hooks/`
- Use Tailwind utility classes for styling — no CSS modules or styled-components
- Use Lucide React for icons — don't add other icon libraries

## SSE handling

- `analyzeCompliance` in `api.ts` reads the SSE stream manually via `ReadableStream`
- Each `data: {json}` line is parsed and passed to an `onResult` callback
- Stream ends on `data: [DONE]` — the `onComplete` callback fires
- Handle `data: {"error": "..."}` lines gracefully in the UI

## Status color palette (defined in index.css @theme)

- `--color-status-met`: green
- `--color-status-not-met`: red
- `--color-status-partial`: amber
- `--color-status-pending`: gray
